         systemd,
         sudo,
         iproute2
Description: System management tool for Debian after automatic login
 A TUI-based system management tool designed to run after automatic
 login on tty1.
 .
 Features:
  - Configure static IP for network interfaces (with systemd-networkd
    persistence)
  - Reboot the system
  - Power off the system
 .
 Auto-login on tty1 is configured via a systemd getty drop-in override.
 The dedicated auto-login user runs this tool via passwordless sudo.
